cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with recognizing events in images. Additionally, it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as it introduces a novel approach for utilizing object detection information in event recognition. The paper also mentions the use of batch pooling, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, since the paper deals with malicious event recognition, it may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
